caption.text: QRreview: The Legend of Zelda: Link's Awakening for Switch. I've seen a few reviews of this Zelda remake focusing on how amazing of a remake it is.. and I couldn't stop thinking: "Yeah, but is it a good game?". So this is my impression of a “Link’s Awakening” as a Zelda virgin.. 😎 .. (ehm 😌) At its core Link's Awakening" is a top-down action and exploration game. You'll explore the world, unlock new skills to access new areas and fight bosses. Part of your exploration are dungeons; these are the best part of the game and offer a mix of puzzles and combat with each having its (small) twist. Combat uses a shield/sword combo with a few other gadgets (like bombs or hook shoot), it's "simplistic", but it works. There's a synergy of gameplay and world-building that just clicks - you want to see more of this lovely toy-world and learn new ways to fight different enemies. As a little-cute Link swing the little-cute sword around frivolously murdering 😈 little-cute enemies. Everything about "Link's Awakening" is "cute" 🍭 It uses diorama-style visuals, with the world having a toy-like look and tilt-shift depth effect makes it feel like you're looking into this mico-Zelda-world. 👏🏼 Followed by a great shader work, real-time lights, particle effects and fantastic (popping) colour work - this is a gorgeous mini-world. + excellent orchestra score of classic Zelda tunes. 🔥 It looks and sounds beautiful, but mostly it’s just a “fun time”.. but ... Well, 2 (buts) in this case. 1. The performance is poor and continuously jumps 60fps/30fps; it is very distracting and happens a lot. 2. This is a $60 game. It's also a relatively (mechanically) a "simple" game — something we see mostly from indie devs nowadays. Taking out the Zelda-nostalgia - for me, around $30 would be a fair price. There’s also a “Zelda-Maker” mode that sounds great, but has no online (viva 1993 😈). Despite the issues: This is an excellent game. I had a blast with "Link's Awakening", it plays smoothly, has a super-charming world and a tons of personality. It's more of an indie-Zelda while we wait for BoTW2 and that's ok. 🔥🔥 Like and comment to win Saturday! 🤟🏻 #zelda #spizakreview #nintendoswitch #linksawakening

No Mario Kart Tour, as corridas são gratuitas e você só paga se quiser comprar pacotes de personagens especiais que, apesar de dar bônus, não são necessários para ganhar. E aí, vamos jogar?

Whoa.. my work just got featured in @pcmagofficial! 🙏🏼🕹 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
“This is what happens when you realize that a fight stick is the only way to play a fighting game, and you want one that's tailor-made for your obsessions. With a custom stick, you aren't limited to what manufacturers choose to sell. Instead, you can select (depending on the stick builder) the case, joystick, gate, button types, and custom art.

Jony Fraze is a highly regarded source for custom sticks. A fighting game fan since the 1990s, Fraze knows what goes into crafting an attractive, well-balanced, and functional stick.

Fraze's prices are on the higher end of the fight stick spectrum, costing roughly $300 to $400, but he makes all his products by hand, and with care. Last year, he built me a beautiful Art of Fighting-themed stick that's compatible with Dreamcast and Neo Geo. It's an excellent option for mixing it up in retro fighting games.” - Jeffrey L. caption.text:
有孔ボードに引き続き、夜な夜な
作成したIKEAの飾り棚。
その上にもらったポスターを貼って一応は完成か？🤔
と自己満に浸りオタク道を順調に？突き進む紙一重おじさん。
しかし絵になるな〜🖼
ふひゃ...。ふひゃひゃ、ふひゃひゃひゃひゃ！！！！
と1人キモ笑いしてたら
後方からバキャキャキャ！！！！
と何かがなぎ倒れた音が。
！？
振り向くと背の高い棚が倒れてファミカセが散乱。
彼らの仕業である。
まぁ怪我なくて良かったな〜💁🏻‍♂️💦
ちゃんと直しておけよー。
とか言って寛容な父親ぶりを息子達に見せつつ、
一緒に片付けてると
ワギャンランド3だけが破損してかのような状態に😅
お陰で中の基盤を見る事が出来ました😇
小学生の時から連れ添ったワギャンランド。
正直妻よりも長い付き合いである。
うう。
ワギャン。
沢山の思い出をありがとう。
きっと...。
きっと僕は君を忘れないだろう...。
R.I.P🙏
ちなみに基盤のみでさしたら案の定つきました。
お帰り。ワギャン笑

⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
According to the developer, the story of the game is set after the Contra III: The Alien Wars and before Contra: Hard Corps.

#Onthisday #1yearago September 25, 2018 #SouthPark #TheStickofTruth was released on #NintendoSwitch. South Park: The Stick of Truth is a  #roleplaying #videogame developed by #ObsidianEntertainment in collaboration with #SouthParkDigitalStudios and published by #Ubisoft. Based on the American adult animated television series South Park, the game follows the New Kid, who has moved to the eponymous town and becomes involved in an epic role-play fantasy war involving humans, wizards, and elves, who are fighting for control of the all-powerful Stick of Truth. Their game quickly escalates out of control and brings them into conflict with aliens, Nazi zombies, and gnomes, threatening the entire town with destruction.

Hori is set to release a Mario Kart Racing Wheel for Nintendo Switch. Two different versions of the wheel will be available, one being described as a "standard" model and the other being a more expensive deluxe model. The accessory will be compatible with both Nintendo Switch and PC, with functions from Switch's Joy-Con and Pro Controllers being available as standard. It also comes with a foot pedal! No news yet on a Western release but you can pre-order it on Play Asia with release date in November in Japan. The standard option will be priced at 6,980 yen (approx. £52 / $65), while the deluxe version will cost 13,980 yen (approx. £104 / $130).

caption.text: #MarioKartTour is now available for Android and iOS. I don't play many games on my phone, but thanks @nintendo for bringing some awesome titles to mobile! It takes a while to get used to steering and drifting, but it's still just as fun as the other entries in the Mario Kart series. Have you played yet?

Mario  Kart Tour - First Opinions
————————————
So Mario Kart Tour came out today for both IOS and Android and it’s honestly alright. It’s pretty much gatcha Mario Kart and in my opinion it doesn’t control all too well. I mean yeah it’s a good waste time in class sort of game and the tracks are honestly pretty nice. I just feel like MKT was unnecessary and I wish Nintendo would’ve used the resources and budget for this game for MK8D DLC. If you want to give this game a shot it’s honestly not too bad similar to Dr Mario World. I’ll give some second opinions once I play a bit more but as it stands it’s a solid 6 or 7 outta 10.
